{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Since the court\u2019s 5-to-4 decision six years ago in Ashcroft v. Iqbal, the rate of early dismissals in cases brought by individuals has risen sharply.", "abstract": "Adam Liptak Sidebar column holds that 2009 Supreme Court decision in Ashcroft v Iqbal, which made it much easier for judges to dismiss civil suits soon after they are filed, has led to sharp rise in early dismissals; says decision, one of most consequential rulings in 10-year tenure of Chief Justice John G Roberts Jr, has had a detrimental effect on individuals, particularly in employment discrimination and civil rights cases.", "section_name": "U.S.", "print_page": "15", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Adam", "role": "reported", "lastname": "LIPTAK", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By ADAM LIPTAK"}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/05/19/us/9-11-ruling-by-supreme-court-has-transformed-civil-lawsuits.html", "lead_paragraph": "Since the court\u2019s 5-to-4 decision six years ago in Ashcroft v. Iqbal, the rate of early dismissals in cases brought by individuals has risen sharply.", "headline": {"print_headline": "Ruling Altered Civil Suits, to Detriment of Individuals", "main": "Supreme Court Ruling Altered Civil Suits, to Detriment of Individuals", "content_kicker": "Sidebar", "kicker": "Sidebar"}, "_id": "5559aa2738f0d8736422853e", "word_count": "942", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2015/05/19/us/19bar-web/19bar-web-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2015/05/19/us/19bar-web/19bar-web-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 401, "url": "images/2015/05/19/us/19bar-web/19bar-web-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/05/19/us/19bar-web/19bar-web-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "401"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2015